{{Infobox college | name = Janaki Medical College | native_name = जानकी मेडिकल कलेज | established = {{start date|2003}} | location = [[Janakpur, Nepal]], {{flagicon|Nepal}} | logo = | image = | motto = to help enhance the quality of life | campus = [[Urban area|Urban]] | type = [[Private university|Private]] | parent = | head_label = Management | head = Ram Janaki Health Foundation | free_label = Alumni | free = Society of Ex-Students | dean = | director = Prof. | affiliations = [[Tribhuvan University]] | website = {{URL|www.janakimedicalcollege.edu.np}} }}
'''Janaki Medical College and Teaching Hospital''' (JMCTH) is a medical school located in Chireshwarnath municipality and city hospital at Brhampuri 9, [[Janakpur, Nepal]]. It provides healthcare education in association with [[Tribhuvan University]] Institute of Medicine<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tribhuvan-university.edu.np/institutes/institute-of-medicine/ |title=Institutes: Institute of Medicine |publisher=Tribhuvan University |accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> and regulated by Nepal Medical Council (NMC).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nmc.org.np/recognized-institution/medical-college.html |title=Recognized Institution - Medical-college |website=www.nmc.org.np |accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> It is managed by Ram Janaki Health Foundation which is registered under the Nepalese company act. The college with established in 2003 with an annual intake of 80 students a year to a MBBS programme.<ref name="KP 10Sep2014">{{cite news |url=http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/news/2014-09-10/janaki-medical-college-loses-mbbs-seats.html |title=Janaki Medical College loses MBBS seats |first=Manish |last=Gautam |work=[[The Kathmandu Post]] |date=10 September 2014 |accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nmc.org.np/institution-info/janaki-medical-college.html |title=Janaki Medical College. Contact Information |website=www.nmc.org.np |accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref>
On 1 January 2014 the NMC barred the college from enrolling students and Tribhuvan University stopped admissions.<ref name="KP 10Sep2014"/> In July 2015, students from the college that were worried about their future protested in Katmandu.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://thehimalayantimes.com/kathmandu/janaki-medical-college-students-stage-protest-near-singha-durbar/ |title=Janaki Medical College students stage protest near Singha Durbar |work=[[The Himalayan Times]] |date=2 July 2015 |accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref>
