[[File:La Mère éducatrice Première Année 1917–18.jpg|thumb|''La mère éducatrice'', the first issue 1917–1918]] '''''La mère éducatrice''''' (meaning ''Motherhood and Education'' in English) was a feminist anarchist magazine founded by [[Madeleine Vernet]].<ref name="mmd">{{cite web|author=Marie-Michèle Doucet|title=Prise de parole au féminin : la paix et les relations internationales dans les revendications du mouvement de femmes pour la paix en France (1919-1934)|url=https://papyrus.bib.umontreal.ca/xmlui/bitstream/handle/1866/13597/Doucet_Marie-Mich%C3%A8le_2015_Th%C3%A8se.pdf?sequence=8&isAllowed=y|publisher=University of Montreal|accessdate=31 January 2017|language=French|format=PhD Thesis|date=May 2015}}</ref> The magazine was first published in October 1917.<ref name="lcg">{{cite journal|title=Et si les mères désertaient la guerre... Madeleine Vernet (1879-1949): pacifisme et féminisme|journal=Les Cahiers du GRIF|date=1976|volume=14|issue=1|language=French}}</ref> The headquarters was in [[Levallois-Perret]].<ref>{{cite web|title=La mère educatrice|url=https://mirlyn.lib.umich.edu/Record/014651704|work=University of Michigan Library|accessdate=31 January 2017}}</ref> Madeleine Vernet also edited the magazine.<ref>{{cite book|author=Norma Valle Ferrer|title=Luisa Capetillo, Pioneer Puerto Rican Feminist|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sVGHD86vO80C&pg=PA47|accessdate=31 January 2017|year=2006|publisher=Peter Lang|isbn=978-0-8204-4285-3|page=47}}</ref> The magazine adopted a [[pacifist]], socialist and educative stance.<ref name="mmd"/><ref>{{cite web|author=Marie-Michèle Doucet|title='Disarmament of Hatred through Children’s Literature: Madeleine Vernet’s tales of peace and reconciliation’|url=http://www.leeds.ac.uk/arts/download/2704/resistance_to_war_conference_abstracts|publisher=Leeds University|accessdate=31 January 2017|date=March 2016}}</ref> It existed until 1939.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vernet, Madeleine (1878-1949)|url=http://cgecaf.ficedl.info/mot17.html|work=Cgecaf|accessdate=31 January 2017|language=French}}</ref>
